  "poem": {
    "content": "A cousin's grief, a warm embrace,\nAn ordinary life, losing its pace.\nA couple, have they found their way?\nOr lost their light in the fading day?\n\nThe arena thrums, a cricket's call,\nA buzzing question, encompassing all.\nWhat is the answer, whispered low?\nTo the outer darkness, where shadows grow?\n\nThe version shattered, a broken dream,\nA lonely heart beside a silent stream.\nThe club is empty, the music gone,\nLeaving echoes until the break of dawn.\n\nA dilemma unfolds, a cruel design,\nTo scrap the future, a love divine.\nOr find the strength to rise anew,\nAnd paint the world in vibrant hue.\nHave hope.",
